<br>
There are thousands of alcohol OD's in this country every year, not even counting drunk driving.  Alcohol is cheap and easy to acquire.  Let's not split hairs here folks, you might have to be 21 to buy it, but when I was 16 it only took me about a half hour to get booze when I wanted it.  Although I've <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>never</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> heard of a 14-year old girl who got pregnant when she had been drinking....... *blink*<br>
<br>
No one has ever died as a direct result of smoking marijuana.  You can't.  The LD50 (lethal dose in 50% of test subjects) is estimated at around 130 pounds of pot eaten in one hour (about 50 pounds if you were to smoke it).  You cannot smoke that much pot.  I know, I've tried.  It's expensive, unless you're buying that mexican green dirt crap, which you really shouldn't be as a) that shit actually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>does</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> go to supporting bad guys south of the border and b) it's not going to get you high.  Thus, unless the kid has tons of money, it's not likely to be that much of a problem.  It can be a real pain in the ass to acquire.  The bounds of what would be considered &quot;common sense&quot; stick around.  I don't want to be making intelligent decisions stoned- it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>is</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a drug here folks, as so many people who smoke it tend to forget- but the risks to alcohol have always struck me as far greater than the risks to pot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=murel>Murel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1301<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/27/03 5:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2121.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I WANT THEM DEAD!</span><hr size=1> I think the drugs=terrorism/violent crime argument is valid for drugs like cocaine/heroin, just not marijuana. I mean, doesn't most cocaine come from South America and smuggled in through various bad ways, and wasn't Taliban-run Afghanistan a major source of heroin?<br>
